Arcane Trap Suppressor	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																						PRESPELL:1,Dispel Magic,Dispel Magic (Greater)						DESC:Your magic can suppress magic traps longer than usual.																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.8	BENEFIT:When you target a magic trap with Dispel Magic or Greater Dispel Magic, if your caster level check exceeds the Disable Device DC of the trap, the trap is disabled for 1d4 minutes.
Close Call			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Deft Hands																										DESC:Your nimble fingers are able to catch small slips before they become big disasters.																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.8	BENEFIT:Once per day, you may reroll either a Disable Device or Sleight of Hand check. You must decide to use this ability after the first attempt but before the results are revealed by the GM. You must take the second roll, even if it's worse.
Coaxing Spell		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Metamagic			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spell Focus (Enchantment)				PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (Dungeoneering)=6														DESC:Your charms and enchantments reach the minds of even the lowliest dungeon denizens.																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.10	BENEFIT:This feat only works with mind-affecting effects. A coaxing spell affects mindless oozes and vermin as if they weren't mindless, but has no effect on other creature types. A coaxing spell uses a spell slot 2 levels higher than the spell's actual level.
Cursed Item Detection	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General															PRESKILL:1,Spellcraft=5				PRESPELL:1,Detect Magic										DESC:Your arcane prowess is so great that even cursed items fail to befuddle you.																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.12	BENEFIT:You gain a +2 bonus on checks made to identify the properties of magic items. In addition, you need only exceed the DC of these checks by 5 in order to determine whether or not an item is cursed.
Dampen Presence		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Skill Focus (Stealth)				PRESKILL:1,Stealth=5																	DESC:Your habitual stillness makes you difficult to perceive for creatures that use blindsight or blindsense.																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.10	BENEFIT:You may use the Stealth skill to hide from any creature attempting to perceive you using blindsight or blindsense, even if you are clearly in that creature's perceptual field. This feat does not confer any advantages against other forms of perception, such as scent, vision, or tremorsense.
Ostentatious Display	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																			DESC:Your extravagant jewelry and accessories give you an air of importance you can use to your advantage in many social situations.																				BONUS:SKILL|Intimidate|1|PREEQUIP:1,TYPE.Belt,TYPE.Shirt,TYPE.Cloak	BONUS:SKILL|Diplomacy|1|PREEQUIP:1,TYPE.Robe,TYPE.Boot,TYPE.Amulet	BONUS:SKILL|Bluff|1|PREEQUIP:1,TYPE.Eyegear,TYPE.Glove,TYPE.Headband	BONUS:SKILL|TYPE.Perform|1|PREEQUIP:1,TYPE.Headgear,TYPE.Ring,TYPE.Bracer							SOURCEPAGE:p.12	BENEFIT:As long as you are wearing a valuable nonmagical item in a magic item slot, you gain a +i bonus on skill checks with a corresponding skill. Bonuses from wearing items in multiple slots that affect the same skill do not stack.
Tactical Reposition	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.AttackOption																																	DESC:You excel at moving foes right where you want them.																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.8	BENEFIT:When making a reposition combat maneuver, you can move an enemy into a trap or other hazardous area, such as a pit, wall scythe, or blade barrier. When you do so, the moved enemy is treated as though it had activated the trap or triggered the hazard, and it takes a -2 penalty to AC and on saving throws to mitigate the trap or hazard's effects.
Torchbearer			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General												PRELEVEL:MIN=5																DEFINE:LeadershipScore|0	DESC:You acquire a professional torchbearer to accompany you into the dungeon.														ABILITY:FEAT|VIRTUAL|Leadership Score	ABILITY:FEAT|VIRTUAL|Leadership|PRELEVEL:MIN=8																																																		BONUS:VAR|LeadershipScore|(TL+CHA)	SOURCEPAGE:p.20
Torch Handling		CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																			DESC:In your grasp, a simple torch becomes a beacon. Torchbearers must take this feat at first level.							AUTO:WEAPONPROF|Torch																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.21	BENEFIT:You gain three benefits upon taking this feat. First, you treat torches as simple weapons. Second, the radius of normal and increased illumination shed by any torch or mundane light source you carry increases by 10 feet. Finally, once per day, you may reroll a single saving throw to resist any effect that would otherwise extinguish your light source.
